	"preview": "<p>Hello and welcome to Notebag! This series of interconnected notes aims to help you get started. Click on any of the links you see in this note to learn more details about that topic. Or just click around and see what you can find! Let's get started.</p><p>Once you're done, feel free to delete them. You can recreate this tutorial at any time from the preferences window!</p><h2>Markdown formatting</h2><p>Notebag supports a wide array of <span data-type=\"zettelkasten_link\" data-unique=\"markdown-formatting-sng316uvz\" class=\"zettelkasten-link\" tabindex=\"0\">markdown formatting</span> options, so you can get your notes to look just right. There's also a few custom extensions that have been added so that <span data-type=\"zettelkasten_link\" data-unique=\"organizing-your-notes-iwbie2kzn\" class=\"zettelkasten-link\" tabindex=\"0\">organizing your notes</span> is easier.</p><h2>Organizing your notes</h2><p>To help you with keeping track of your notes you have categories and a Zettelkasten system at your hands. Every note can be assigned an infinite number of tags and can link to any other note of your choosing. To find out how it all works see: <span data-type=\"zettelkasten_link\" data-unique=\"organizing-your-notes-zn4rtms5q\" class=\"zettelkasten-link\" tabindex=\"0\">organizing your notes</span></p><h2>Importing existing notes</h2><p>Notebag can import your existing notes from another app, if you have it as a folder of .md files. The file name decides the title of the note. If you have any images added to your note, make sure they are in a folder that has the same name as the note. The directory structure should look roughly like this:</p><pre class=\"hljs plaintext\" data-language=\"plaintext\"><code>import/\n  My Note 1.md\n  My Note 2.md\n  My Note 2/\n    image-01.png\n    image-02.jpg</code></pre><p>Once you're ready to import, head over to the Preferences pane (<code>Command/Ctrl+,</code>) and check the \"Notes\" section. There you can find an \"Import\" button.</p><h2>Common keyboard shortcuts</h2><p>You can navigate Notebag entirely with your keyboard. As part of this there's a few <span data-type=\"zettelkasten_link\" data-unique=\"keyboard-shortcuts-ry0twfpa4\" class=\"zettelkasten-link\" tabindex=\"0\">keyboard shortcuts</span> you'll want to get familiar with. Of course, you can also do everything with your mouse.</p><ul><li><p><code>Ctrl+Alt+Space</code> - Show and hide the Notebag window</p></li><li><p><code>Command/Ctrl+N</code> - Create a new note</p></li><li><p><code>Command/Ctrl+D</code> - Delete the currently active note</p></li><li><p><code>Command/Ctrl+F</code> - Search/replace in currently active note</p></li><li><p><code>Command/Ctrl+P</code> - Open the <span data-type=\"zettelkasten_link\" data-unique=\"omnibar-0cd35trlh\" class=\"zettelkasten-link\" tabindex=\"0\">omnibar</span></p></li><li><p><code>Command/Ctrl+,</code> - Open the preferences</p></li><li><p><code>Command/Ctrl+Shift+L</code> - Switch between light and dark mode</p></li><li><p><code>Command/Alt+1-3</code> - Switches between writing, note overview and project overview</p></li><li><p><code>Command/Alt+4-9</code> - Switches to your pinned projects</p></li><li><p><code>Command/Alt+0</code> - Switches to the note archive.</p></li></ul><p>Most of the keyboard shortcuts can be changed in the preferences window.</p><h2>Omnibar</h2><p>Notebag comes with a feature that many software developers probably know from their code editor: The <span data-type=\"zettelkasten_link\" data-unique=\"omnibar-2qmsiome1\" class=\"zettelkasten-link\" tabindex=\"0\">omnibar</span> - It helps you quickly find notes and common actions while you're typing away. You can give it a try by pressing <code>Command/Ctrl+P</code>!</p><h2>That's all</h2><p>If you've read through all the notes you now know everything about Notebag! This is the point at which I'll leave you and wish you a lot of fun in creating your notes. I hope Notebag is as useful to you, as it is to me!</p><p>~ Richard, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/pretzelhds\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" tabindex=\"0\">@pretzelhds</a></p><p><span class=\"category-pill\" data-type=\"category\" tabindex=\"0\">tutorial</span></p>",
